Rating: 3
A very simple, lovely treat! The pear is a very mild and mellow flavor which is a perfect match for the cardamom. I used the seeds from 2 cardamom pods and it was perfect. Consistency was much better on day 1--it got a little too icy in my freezer overnight. Still delicious though.

Rating: 4
This benefits from making the base at least 24 hours in advance and letting the cardamom really infuse the nectar. Served it after Thanksgiving dinner for a palate refresher. It's great other time with ginger cookies.

